# Predicates:
Mammal(x) ::: x is a mammal.
HasTeeth(x) ::: x has teeth.
Platypus(x) ::: x is a platypus.
Human(x) ::: x is a human.

# Premises:
∀x (Mammal(x) ∧ ¬HasTeeth(x) → ∃y (Mammal(y) ∧ HasTeeth(y))) ::: Some mammals have teeth.
∀x (Platypus(x) → ¬HasTeeth(x)) ::: Platypus have no teeth.
∀x (Platypus(x) → Mammal(x)) ::: Platypus are mammals.
Human(h) ∧ HasTeeth(h) ::: Humans have teeth.

# Conclusion:
¬Platypus(x) ∨ ¬Mammal(x) ∨ ¬HasTeeth(x) ∨ ¬Human(x) ∨ Reptile(x)
